        ("Portals", "What does the Portals page do?",
            "Go to Portals in the sidebar. It stores your TRACES, IT Portal and TIN-NSDL login credentials (AES-encrypted). Use the Open button on each card to launch the portal in your browser. Credentials are never sent to any server — they are stored only on your machine."),
        ("Portals", "How do I open TRACES or IT Portal quickly?",
            "Go to Portals → click the browser icon on the TRACES or IT Portal card. It opens the portal URL in your default browser. Your saved credentials are shown so you can copy-paste them."),
        ("Portals", "What is the TRACES Downloads folder?",
            "The TRACES Downloads folder is where CDeTDS looks for Conso files, Form 16A text files, and other downloads from TRACES. Click 'Downloads Folder' on the TRACES card to open it directly. Save all TRACES exports here for easy import."),

